      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Excellent! Now I have a LOT of critical information. Let me compile the findings:\n\n**KEY FINDINGS:**\n\n1. **WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR BSOD** - From the photo (stop code confirmed)\n\n2. **Kernel-Power Event ID 41** (Critical) - Multiple instances:\n   - 03/07/2026 16:15:04 - System rebooted without proper shutdown\n   - 03/07/2026 10:09:11 - System rebooted without proper shutdown\n   - 20/06/2026 09:41:22 - System rebooted without proper shutdown\n   - 20/06/2026 05:09:46 - System rebooted without proper shutdown\n   - 17/06/2026 19:40:10 - System rebooted without proper shutdown\n\n3. **WER-SystemErrorReporting Event ID 1001** - Specific BSOD error codes:\n   - 20/06/2026 05:14:23: **0x0000012b** (WHEA_UNCORRECTABLE_ERROR) with parameters (0xffffffffc00002c4, 0x00000000000004fc, 0x000002be843b5c00, 0xffff95818607a000) - dump saved to C:\\WINDOWS\\MEMORY.DMP\n   - 17/06/2026 19:46:48: **0x000000be** (ATTEMPTED_WRITE_TO_READONLY_MEMORY)\n\n4. **volmgr Event ID 161** - Dump file creation FAILED multiple times:\n   - 03/07/2026 16:14:58\n   - 03/07/2026 10:09:04\n   - 20/06/2026 05:09:39 (twice)\n   - 17/06/2026 19:40:06\n\n5. **Volsnap Event ID 35** - Volume shadow copy errors (repeated):\n   - 02/07/2026, 30/06/2026, 25/06/2026 - \"Le copie shadow del volume C: sono state interrotte. Impossibile espandere l'archivio delle copie shadow.\"\n\n6. **WER-SystemErrorReporting**: \"Il file di paging è troppo piccolo per essere completato\" (Paging file too small)\n\n7. **Resource-Exhaustion-Detector Event ID 2004** - Multiple low virtual memory conditions:\n   - chrome.exe using1-3GB, vmmem using ~1GB, opencode.exe using ~790MB\n   - The system is running out of virtual memory frequently\n\n8. **Kernel-Boot Event 20**: \"Ultimo stato di arresto riuscito: false\" - Last shutdown was NOT clean\n\n9. **XTU3SERVICE timeout** - Intel XTU service failing to start consistently. This is Intel's Extreme Tuning Utility service.\n\n**Hardware:**\n- HP OMEN Laptop 15-ce0xx\n- CPU: Intel Core i5-7300HQ (4C/4T, 2.5GHz)\n- RAM: 16GB (2x8GB, SK Hynix + Samsung, 2400MHz - mixed vendors!)\n- GPU: Intel HD 630 + NVIDIA GeForce GTX 1050\n- NVIDIA driver: 31.0.15.3179 (April 2023 - very outdated!)\n- Intel GPU driver: 31.0.101.2140 (November 2025 - recent)\n- Firmware: AMI F.24, HP 838F\n- No minidump files exist (all in C:\\Windows\\Minidump are Chrome/explorer user-mode dumps, not kernel dumps)\n\nNow let me also check disk health and paging file settings.",
